BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-0-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T180000
SUMMARY:Pick you up
DESCRIPTION:Vámonos\, mi amor. The weekend starts now. ✨\n\nIll be outside at 6 — text me when you are coming down.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-1-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T203000
SUMMARY:Reset at the apartment
DESCRIPTION:Casa. Drop the bags\, breathe.\n\nWe will swing by Erewhon on the way — steak\, buffalo cauli\, two big waters. The desert can wait until tomorrow.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-2-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T203000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T213000
SUMMARY:Workout together
DESCRIPTION:Light\, easy\, fun. We have got horses and hikes ahead — no need to leave it all on the floor tonight\, mi vida.\n\nMobility\, stretch\, dance a little. Whatever feels good.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-3-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T213000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T223000
SUMMARY:Steak + buffalo cauli at home
DESCRIPTION:Cooking for you. No delivery\, no rush. Just us in the kitchen.\n\nSteak\, rice\, the buffalo cauli you love from Erewhon. Te voy a consentir esta noche.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-4-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T223000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260515T233000
SUMMARY:Harry Potter\, just one hour
DESCRIPTION:Couch\, blanket\, you on me. One hour\, that is the deal — we save the rest for the desert nights.\n\nDescansa\, mi reina. Tomorrow is going to be a beautiful day.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-5-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T063000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T073000
SUMMARY:Wake up\, breakfast at home
DESCRIPTION:Buenos días\, hermosa. ☀️\n\nEggs\, toast\, fruit\, coffee. Slow start. The desert is not going anywhere.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-6-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T073000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T081500
SUMMARY:Pack the car\, head out
DESCRIPTION:Picnic blanket\, sunscreen\, water\, snacks. Light load — we buy fresh in JT.\n\nDownload offline Google Maps before we leave. Listo? Vámonos.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-7-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T121500
SUMMARY:Joshua Tree Farmers Market 🍓
LOCATION:61651 Twentynine Palms Hwy\, Joshua Tree\, CA 92252
DESCRIPTION:Our first stop in the desert. Sábado en el mercado\, contigo.\n\nWe are buying:\n• Fresh berries (strawberries\, blueberries\, blackberries)\n• Stone fruit if in season (peaches\, plums)\n• Cold-press juice if a vendor has it\n• Snacks for our picnic blanket later\n\nMarket closes at 1 PM sharp.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-8-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T123000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T134500
SUMMARY:Thrifting + wash berries
LOCATION:Hwy 62\, Joshua Tree\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Walkable strip — tu turno\, mi amor\, you lead the way.\n\n• JT Trading Post (Ivonne is right here)\n• The End / Hoof and The Horn / Ricochet\n\nWhile we are out\, wash the berries at a public restroom — Frontier Cafe\, JT Coffee Co.\, or the Visitor Center (6554 Park Blvd). Pat dry with paper towels\, back in the bag.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-9-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T144500
SUMMARY:🍓 Berry picnic at Noah Purifoy
LOCATION:63030 Blair Ln\, Joshua Tree\, CA 92252
DESCRIPTION:Picnic en el desierto\, mi vida.\n\nPicnic blanket from the car\, berries + fruit + snacks from the market. Sit outside under the sky\, eat with our hands\, no plates\, no fuss.\n\nSnuzzu next to us — softest blanket setup ever.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-10-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T144500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T154500
SUMMARY:Noah Purifoy Outdoor Desert Art
LOCATION:63030 Blair Ln\, Joshua Tree\, CA 92252
DESCRIPTION:Free\, open daily. 10 acres of upside-down bikes and beautiful weird things.\n\nThe afternoon light is going to love you. Qué linda te ves hoy.\n\nYour fit: cowboy hat\, brown pants\, sunglasses.\nMy fit: white shoes\, white shirt\, green shorts.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-11-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T161000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T173000
SUMMARY:Pioneertown wander
LOCATION:Pioneertown\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Old west on the main street. Easy walking\, your hand in mine\, the kind of slow pace I miss when life gets fast.\n\nCoffee at Frontier Cafe Pioneertown if we need a boost before sunset.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-12-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T181500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T195000
SUMMARY:🌅 Sunset at Transmission
LOCATION:Joshua Tree\, CA
DESCRIPTION:This one. 7:40 PM sunset\, but we get there 90 minutes early to find the spot.\n\nGolden hour into blue hour. Just us\, the desert\, and the sky doing the thing.\n\nMi favorita. The shot of the trip.\n\nMy fit: black shirt\, black shorts.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-13-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T203000
SUMMARY:Cheap dinner — your pick
DESCRIPTION:Tu eliges\, mi reina. Three options\, all good:\n\n• In-N-Out\, Yucca Valley — cheeseburgers\, animal fries (~$20)\n• La Taqueria de Joshua Tree — al pastor\, carne asada (~$25)\n• Crossroads Cafe — if you want something a little healthier\n\nSaving the nice dinner for tomorrow.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-14-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260516T230000
SUMMARY:Car camp + Harry Potter 🎬
DESCRIPTION:BLM dispersed camping right outside the park (check iOverlander\, Section 6).\n\nLaptop on the dash\, blankets\, market snacks. You curled into me\, the desert stars above the windshield.\n\nNo notifications. No work. Solo tú y yo. This is the part of the trip I think about when I am tired.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-15-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T063000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T070000
SUMMARY:Wake up in the desert
DESCRIPTION:Buenos días\, mi amor. The horses are waiting.\n\nCoffee already in the thermos. Pack the car — we are not coming back to this spot. The day ahead is going to be one we tell people about.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-16-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T073000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T093000
SUMMARY:🐴 Sunrise horseback at Cascade Trails
LOCATION:Cascade Trails Mustang Sanctuary\, Joshua Tree\, CA
DESCRIPTION:This is the one I have been thinking about for you\, vaquera.\n\nCascade Trails Mustang Sanctuary\n(760) 910-7220 · @cascadetrails_jt\nmustangsanctuary.com\n\nWe arrive at 7:00. ~2 hour ride through mustang country in the soft morning light.\n\nYour fit: dark jeans\, white linen blouse\, brown belt\, cowboy hat\, boots. Te vas a ver hermosa — I already know.\n\nMine: jeans (no shorts)\, boots\, hat.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-17-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T100000
SUMMARY:Coffee + split a burrito
LOCATION:Joshua Tree Coffee Co.\, 61738 Twentynine Palms Hwy\, Joshua Tree\, CA
DESCRIPTION:Best small-batch in town. Pour-over and ONE breakfast burrito to split — light fuel before the hikes\, mi vida.\n\nReservation tonight at 5:30 PM\, do not want to be too full.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-18-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T113000
SUMMARY:Hidden Valley Loop
LOCATION:Hidden Valley Trailhead\, Joshua Tree NP
DESCRIPTION:1 mile loop\, easy\, shaded between giant boulders. Tranquila — we start with the gentle one while it is still cool.\n\nClassic JT terrain. The kind of place that makes you forget what day it is.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-19-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T113500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T120000
SUMMARY:Hall of Horrors
LOCATION:Hall of Horrors\, Joshua Tree NP
DESCRIPTION:5 minutes down the road. We squeeze through the slot in the rocks — sounds scary\, looks incredible. Quick stop\, 20 min tops.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-20-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T121500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T131500
SUMMARY:Keys View
LOCATION:Keys View\, Joshua Tree NP
DESCRIPTION:Up high. On clear days you can see all the way to Mexico — the Salton Sea\, the Coachella Valley laid out below us.\n\nSnack break with the market fruit at the top. The wind is going to mess up your hair and you are still going to look beautiful.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-21-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T150000
SUMMARY:Heart Rock + Arch Rock
LOCATION:Arch Rock Trailhead\, Joshua Tree NP
DESCRIPTION:Same trailhead\, 1.4 mile loop. Two rocks\, two photos\, one trail.\n\nHeart Rock is for us. Una foto contigo ahí — that one is going on the wall.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-22-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T151500
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T154500
SUMMARY:Skull Rock
LOCATION:Skull Rock\, Joshua Tree NP
DESCRIPTION:Right off the road. Quick photo\, then we are officially done hiking. Lo logramos.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-23-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T190000
SUMMARY:🌟 Kitchen in the Desert
LOCATION:6427 Mesquite Ave\, Twentynine Palms\, CA 92277
DESCRIPTION:Our nice dinner. The one we earned today.\n\nCaribbean / New American\, sharing plates\, outdoor seating under the desert sky. A glass of wine\, your hand in mine across the table.\n\nReservation confirmed under my name\, 5:30 PM. ✓\n\nGracias por este día contigo\, mi amor.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-24-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260517T220000
SUMMARY:Drive to Laguna + car camp
DESCRIPTION:3 hours. The last of Harry Potter on audio for the road. You will probably fall asleep on my shoulder somewhere past Riverside\, and that is okay.\n\nFree overnight spot near Treasure Island Beach or Crystal Cove. Wake up to the ocean tomorrow.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-25-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260518T070000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260518T080000
SUMMARY:Wake up in Laguna
DESCRIPTION:Beach walk together — 20 min\, salt air\, slow. The reset before the week starts.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-26-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260518T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260518T100000
SUMMARY:Gym + shower (with you)
DESCRIPTION:Free trial day at Equinox Newport Beach\, Crunch Laguna Niguel\, or Anytime — I will call when we wake up.\n\nWorkout\, real shower\, finally. Juntos.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:jt-27-20260516T020606Z@timewellspent
DTSTAMP:20260516T020606Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260518T103000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260518T170000
SUMMARY:Work from Happy Coffee Club
LOCATION:Happy Coffee Club
DESCRIPTION:Heads-down day. Important meetings stacked — Happy Coffee Club has the quiet vibe I need.\n\nIf you want to work next to me\, I would love that.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR